t: And*p Moses went up from the plains of Moab unto the mountain of Nebo, to the top of Pisgah, that is over against Jericho. And the Lord*s shewed him all the land of Gilead, unto Dan,
And*p all Naphtali, and the land of Ephraim, and Manasseh, and all the land of Judah, unto the utmost sea,
And*p the south, and the plain of the valley of Jericho, the city of palm trees, unto Zoar.

And*p the Lord*s said unto him, This is the land which I sware unto Abraham, unto Isaac, and unto Jacob, saying, I will give it unto thy seed: I have caused thee to see it with thine eyes, but thou shalt not go over thither.
So*p Moses the servant of the Lord*s died there in the land of Moab, according to the word of the Lord.*s
And*p he buried him in a valley in the land of Moab, over against Bethâ€“peor: but no man knoweth of his sepulchre unto this day.
And*p Moses was an hundred and twenty years old when he died: his eye was not dim, nor his natural force abated.
And*p the children of Israel wept for Moses in the plains of Moab thirty days: so the days of weeping and mourning for Moses were ended.
And*p Joshua the son of Nun was full of the spirit of wisdom; for Moses had laid his hands upon him: and the children of Israel hearkened unto him, and did as the Lord*s commanded Moses.
And*p there arose not a prophet since in Israel like unto Moses, whom the Lord*s knew face to face,
In*p all the signs and the wonders, which the Lord*s sent him to do in the land of Egypt to Pharaoh, and to all his servants, and to all his land,
And*p in all that mighty hand, and in all the great terror which Moses shewed in the sight of all Israel.
